cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL

The paper focuses on attention management systems, which are primarily concerned with human-computer interaction and user experience. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques and mathematical models of human attention, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses information retrieval and natural language processing, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
